{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/docs/guide/hybrid-syntax","webpackCompilationHash":"ea40f35b618795591751","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/docs/guide/hybrid-syntax"},"id":"b1f04a88-f600-5afb-8cc8-9c8aff48eb66","html":"<h2 id=\"writing-css-with-fragments\"><a href=\"#writing-css-with-fragments\" aria-label=\"writing css with fragments permalink\" class=\"post-toc-anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Writing css with fragments</h2>\n<p>CSS blocks are usually shaped using the <code>{</code> and <code>}</code> characters. Since they are used for JSX assignment expressions, we leverage on fragments in order to write our CSS blocks.</p>\n<h4 id=\"why-fragments-\"><a href=\"#why-fragments-\" aria-label=\"why fragments  permalink\" class=\"post-toc-anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Why fragments ?</h4>\n<p>Fragments create quite a small footprint when writing CSS. With indentation, it becomes as readable as the original CSS syntax.</p>\n<p>Fragments can also be used for interpolated CSS p